                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17742735" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 09:38:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andrea, do you have an example somewhere&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17742738" author="ancosen" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 09:49:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The only thing I&apos;ve tried is by exporting this project: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel-kamelets-examples/tree/main/jbang/postgresql-gcp-secret-refresh&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel-kamelets-examples/tree/main/jbang/postgresql-gcp-secret-refresh&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I exported that to SB and Quarkus with something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
jbang -Dcamel.jbang.version=4.0.0-RC1 camel@apache/camel export --secrets-refresh --secrets-refresh-providers=gcp --runtime=spring-boot --gav=com.github.oscerd:gcp-test:1.0-SNAPSHOT  --directory=/home/oscerd/workspace/gcp-quarkus/ --spring-boot-version=3.1.1 postgresql-log.yaml gcp-sec-refresh.properties
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and then move the gcp-sec-refresh.properties into application.properties&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It could also be enough to run this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot-examples/tree/main/aws-secrets-manager&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot-examples/tree/main/aws-secrets-manager&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but adding the following properties to the application.properties&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
camel.vault.aws.refreshEnabled=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
camel.vault.aws.refreshPeriod=60000
camel.vault.aws.secrets=Secret
camel.main.context-reload-enabled = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;but you will always need to create the secret on AWS Secrets Manager&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17742760" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 11:07:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Try with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;camel.springboot.context-reload-enabled = true&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you need to use camel.springboot instead of camel.main when using SB&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17742774" author="ancosen" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 11:50:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was already there the file is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
camel.springboot.sourceLocationEnabled=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
camel.springboot.modeline=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
camel.vault.gcp.projectId=...
camel.vault.gcp.serviceAccountKey = ...
camel.vault.gcp.refreshEnabled=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
camel.vault.gcp.refreshPeriod=10000
camel.vault.gcp.secrets=database*
camel.vault.gcp.subscriptionName=sub-gcp-sec-refresh
camel.springboot.context-reload-enabled=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17742775" author="ancosen" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 11:51:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t call the refresh task&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17742800" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2023 13:02:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay lets look at this tomorrow&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17743082" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 14 Jul 2023 09:55:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay so I have fixed this - the configureVault needed to be called when you run outside camel-jbang/camel-main. Setting these options was correct already by SB starter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
